ul beaches. The journey is about 2.5 to 3 hours by car from Phnom Penh.</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Recommended Rental:</strong> A compact SUV or a crossover would be ideal for this trip, as it offers a good balance of comfort, space, and the ability to handle some of the less paved roads in the rural areas around Kampot.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<h4><strong>5. Mondulkiri Province</strong></h4>\\n<p>For the adventurous traveler, Mondulkiri offers a more rugged and remote road trip experience. Located in the eastern highlands of Cambodia, Mondulkiri is famous for its rolling hills, waterfalls, and opportunities to interact with rescued elephants. The trip from Phnom Penh takes around 6-7 hours and passes through some off-the-beaten-path areas.</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Recommended Rental:</strong> A 4x4 or a durable SUV is essential for navigating the unpaved roads in this region, especially if you plan on visiting the waterfalls and remote villages.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Renting the right car for your Cambodian road trip ensures that you travel in comfort and safety, no matter the destination. Whether you\'re exploring temples, beaches, or remote countryside, a reliable vehicle will help you experience the beauty of Cambodia to the fullest.</p>\"}',NULL,NULL),
(207,228,'blogs','9','{\"content\":\"<h3><strong>Best Cars for Off-Road Adventures in Cambodia</strong></h3>\\n<p>Cambodia&rsquo;s diverse landscape includes lush forests, rolling hills, and rugged terrain, making it a great destination for off-road enthusiasts. Whether you&rsquo;re heading to remote areas or exploring national parks, choosing the right rental vehicle is essential. Here are some of the best cars for off-road adventures in Cambodia:</p>\\n<h4><strong>1. Toyota Land Cruiser</strong></h4>\\n<p>The Toyota Land Cruiser is built for tough terrains, making it ideal for navigating the rough, unpaved roads found in Cambodia&rsquo;s rural areas. Its strong suspension and all-wheel drive system provide stability and comfort even in challenging conditions.</p>\\n<h4><strong>2. Ford Ranger</strong></h4>\\n<p>The Ford Ranger pickup truck is perfect for those looking to venture into the more remote regions of Cambodia, such as the mountains of Mondulkiri or the jungle trails in Ratanakiri. Its durability and cargo space make it a reliable choice for off-road trips.</p>\\n<h4><strong>3. Mitsubishi Pajero</strong></h4>\\n<p>Known for its 4x4 capability and ruggedness, the Mitsubishi Pajero is excellent for off-road trails and uneven roads. With ample space and advanced safety features, it\'s also a great option for families looking for adventure in the countryside.</p>\\n<h4><strong>4. Toyota Hilux</strong></h4>\\n<p>The Toyota Hilux pickup is another tough, versatile vehicle that can handle both city driving and off-road excursions. Whether you\'re driving through dirt roads or crossing rivers, this durable car can take you to places most others can&rsquo;t.</p>\\n<p>Renting an off-road capable vehicle allows you to fully experience Cambodia\'s beautiful and rugged landscapes, ensuring that your adventure is safe and enjoyable.</p>\",\"status\":\"published\"}','{\"content\":\"<h3><strong>Best Cars for Off-Road Adventures in Cambodia</strong></h3>\\n<p>Cambodia&rsqu