(680,994,'directus_files','3ace148f-fb87-4f18-b272-1aba14ba2105','{\"folder\":\"afdc5f08-5dcf-4e68-a445-11fca7fa8b7b\",\"title\":\"Designer\",\"filename_download\":\"Designer.jpeg\",\"type\":\"image/jpeg\",\"storage\":\"local\"}','{\"folder\":\"afdc5f08-5dcf-4e68-a445-11fca7fa8b7b\",\"title\":\"Designer\",\"filename_download\":\"Designer.jpeg\",\"type\":\"image/jpeg\",\"storage\":\"local\"}',NULL,NULL),
(681,995,'blogs','7','{\"id\":7,\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"user_created\":\"8bf1a523-5059-4ece-8f55-cc361500b3d0\",\"date_created\":\"2024-10-11T11:45:08.000Z\",\"user_updated\":\"8bf1a523-5059-4ece-8f55-cc361500b3d0\",\"date_updated\":\"2024-11-20T02:11:20.000Z\",\"content\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">Family vacations are all about fun and making memories, but planning the logistics&mdash;like renting the right car&mdash;can make all the difference. Here&rsquo;s what you need to consider when renting a car for your next family getaway:</span></p>\\n<h4 style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\"><strong>1. Size Matters</strong></span></h4>\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">For family trips, space is crucial. A larger vehicle like a minivan or an SUV will provide ample room for passengers, luggage, and any extra gear like strollers or sports equipment.</span></p>\\n<h4 style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\"><strong>2. Safety First</strong></span></h4>\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">Make sure the rental car is equipped with important safety features, especially if you&rsquo;re traveling with young children. Look for cars with advanced safety technologies such as backup cameras, lane departure warnings, and plenty of airbags.</span></p>\\n<h4 style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\"><strong>3. Entertainment Options</strong></span></h4>\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">Long trips can be tough on kids, so consider renting a car with built-in entertainment systems. DVD players, Bluetooth audio, or USB ports to charge devices can keep everyone entertained for hours.</span></p>\\n<h4 style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\"><strong>4. Plan for Comfort</strong></span></h4>\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">Check that the car has comfortable seating and climate control, especially if you&rsquo;re going on a long road trip. Adjustable seating and dual-zone air conditioning can make a big difference in keeping everyone happy during the drive.</span></p>\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 12pt;\\\">Renting the right car for your family vacation ensures a smooth and enjoyable trip, with plenty of space and comfort for everyone!</span></p>\",\"title\":\"Renting a Car for Family Vacations: What You Need to Know\",\"description\":\"Family vacations require careful planning. This blog focuses on what to look for when renting a car for your family, from safety features and extra space to entertainment options for kids.\",\"tags\":null,\"thumbnail\":\"3ace148f-fb87-4f18-b272-1aba14ba2105\"}','{\"thumbnail\":\"3ace148f-fb87-4f18-b272-1aba14ba2105\",\"user_updated\":\"8bf1a523-5059-4ece-8f55-cc361500b3d0\",\"date_updated\":\"2024-11-20T02:11:20.564Z\"}',NULL,NULL),
